def is_alien_sorted(words, order):
    alien_order = {char: i for i, char in enumerate(order)}

    for i in range(1, len(words)):
        for j in range(len(words[i - 1])):
            if j == len(words[i]):
                return False

            if words[i - 1][j] != words[i][j]:
                if alien_order[words[i - 1][j]] > alien_order[words[i][j]]:
                    return False
                break

    return True
```

    The algorithm first creates a mapping of the alien alphabet to their respective orders using a dictionary/map. Then, it loops through the given words, checking if they are sorted lexicographically. It compares each character of the adjacent words using the alien alphabet order. If any unordered pair is found, it returns false. If the loop completes, it returns true, indicating the words are sorted lexicographically in the alien language.

